    "narrative": "For our April 13th slate, **Corbin Carroll** leads the charge with an elite 85.94 score, benefiting significantly from a favorable matchup against Dean Kremer and a 16% park factor boost that makes him our must-start anchor. Alongside him, **Jose Caballero** (71.90) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (67.92) provide the high-upside speed element Ghost Ride the WHIP relies on; both are positioned to exploit Yusei Kikuchi\u2019s profile, with **Jose Caballero** in particular receiving a 13% boost for a favorable platoon split. While the lineup is currently \"pending,\" these projections account for expected batting order shifts that favor **Giancarlo Stanton** (65.85) and **Trevor Story** (62.41), the latter of whom maintains a strong score despite the challenge of facing Bailey Ober, thanks to a 12% SP skill rating adjustment.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves the utility slot and the bench. **Max Muncy** (45.06) was the last man out, falling just short of displacing **Dalton Rushing** (44.99). While **Max Muncy** draws a high park factor against Nathan Eovaldi, the optimizer prioritized the floor consistency of **Dalton Rushing** given the current wind conditions. We are monitoring **James Wood** (48.27) and **Seiya Suzuki** (50.33) closely; both face sub-3.20 xERA pitchers, meaning their start is contingent on maintaining their projected batting order slots. Risks remain high for **James Wood**, as facing Paul Skenes carries a 19% penalty to our expected efficiency. We are also tracking **Mickey Moniak**, **Brice Turang**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who are unavailable today due to schedule gaps, forcing us to lean heavily on our active bench depth if late-breaking lineup news shifts the projections for players like **Alex Freeland** or **Austin Riley**.",
